# Algorithm Competition Commit Message
# =====================================
# feat:     New algorithm solution or feature
# fix:      Bug fix in existing solution
# refactor: Code refactoring without functionality change
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
# test:     Adding or updating tests
# chore:    Maintenance tasks, build config, etc.

# Subject line (required)
# ----------------------
# - Use imperative mood: "Add" not "Added" or "Adds"
# - First letter lowercase
# - No period at the end
# - Keep under 50 characters

# Body (optional)
# ---------------
# - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# - Wrap at 72 characters
# - Use bullet points for multiple changes

# Examples:
# ---------
# feat: add LeetCode two sum solution
#
# - Implement hash map approach with O(n) time complexity
# - Add test cases for edge conditions
# - Update README with problem description

# fix: correct off-by-one error in binary search
#
# The binary search implementation had an off-by-one error
# when handling empty arrays. This fix ensures proper bounds
# checking.

# refactor: optimize memory usage in graph traversal
#
# - Replace adjacency matrix with adjacency list
# - Reduce memory usage from O(n^2) to O(n + m)
# - Maintain same time complexity